cience environmental science and archaeometry sample preparation labs the ssrl structural molecular biology smb sample preparation laboratories are available to users by prearrangement to use a laboratory users must complete laboratory training and provide a list of all chemicals to be brought used or stored in the sample preparation laboratory for details contact cynthia patty 650 926 3925 scientific applications selected results august 2010 unusual structure found for an organic semiconductor april 2010 reducing fuel cell costs by changing the structure and reactivity of platinum february 2010 researchers rediscover the structure of water november 2009 stanford led research helps overcome barrier for organic electronics september 2009 leslie jimison receives klein award july 2009 molecular mixing in organic solar cells march 2007 ancient warriors and the origin of chinese purple october 2006 structural sequestration of uranium in bacteriogenic manganese oxides august 2006 hydrogen key to a sustainable future november 2004 structural studies of catalytically stabilized industrial hydrotreating catalysts november 2003 remediation of uranium contaminated water at fry canyon utah september 2003 synchrotron mesodiffraction a tool for understanding turbine engine foreign object damage engineering notes http www ssrl slac stanford edu safety beamlines bl2 ssrl beamlines user admin safety last updated 27 jan 2011 content owner bart johnson page editor lisa dunn
